message.content:
The mine-workings lie north of the town," said Dan. "If we head west we ought to cut the trail leading from Gilby to the north."

So we swung west, making slow going over rough country, sliding on shale & climbing down into draws, circling a big mesa by a
four or five mile valley, sandy-floored. It got hotter as the day wore on and we rested gratefully by a small creek where we watered the horses and drank enough to cure our thirst.
